  "text": "For collision avoidance, utilizing satellite-based radar for UASs has been studied in [CITATION_1] . A modified Automatic Dependent Surveillance-Broadcast (ADS-B) system is used. The main objective of the research is to ensure the safety of NAS through the co-existence of UAVs with other aircraft. The proposed ADS-B satellite radar satisfies this objective by sharing the situational awareness information among all the aircraft. This area of research is essential due to the requirements of UAS integration into NAS and for faster improvements in the future ADS-B systems.",
